data.description: THE most adorable one story ranch home located in the Woodcrest neighborhood of Live Oak.  Light, bright, welcoming, you feel all the good vibes as you walk through the front door.  Beautiful teal cabinets in the eat in kitchen. Breakfast bar flows into the living space. Wood burning brick fireplace to enjoy the soon to be chilly Texas evenings.  Entertain effortlessly in this thoughtfully layed out living space.  Plenty of room in the primary suite that has dual vanities, a walk in closet and a continued cool vibe with sage painted cabinets.  Both bathrooms have upgraded tile in the shower,  along with upgraded faucets, lighting fixtures, and cabinet hardware as well.  Completely redone covered patio (2023).  Additional concrete patio with wood posts strung with cafe lights, perfect for dining outside.  Beautiful, flat backyard with the most majestic oak tree.  Larger fence gate to access backyard through the side.  New roof installed 2022.  Less than 1 mile from the almost 32 acre Woodcrest Nature Park surrounded by trees, jogging trails, unpaved trails, a playground, picnic tables, and workout stations.  Just over a mile to the 75 acre Main City Park that houses a lake (allowing paddle boarding, kayaking and canoeing) stocked twice a year with fish, fishing pier, walking trails, gazebos, a football field, basketball court, skateboarding park, 3 baseball fields, multiple playscapes, a disc golf course, picnic tables and barbecue pits.  Less than 2 miles from the Live Oak City Pool.  Close access to IH 35, 1604, The Forum Shopping Center and Randolph Air Force Base.  Short drive to Morgan's Wonderland, Toyota Field, and Commanche Lookout Park.
